  <section class="container py-5">

    <!-- About Us Section -->
    <h2 class="mt-4 mb-4 fw-bold">About Us</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span> is an independent not-for-profit organisation based in Melbourne.
      We started computer refurbishment in 1998. Our low-cost computers are refurbished by skilled volunteers for Australian Concession Card holders and other eligible customers.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      We install Linux on all computers, ensuring they come with a selection of free software suitable for home, educational, and small business use.
      We offer computers at minimal cost while promoting sustainable e-waste reduction.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Our Mission</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Our goal is to provide affordable computing solutions while reducing electronic waste.
      By refurbishing donated computers, we extend their usability and keep technology accessible.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">How You Can Help</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      <strong>Donate:</strong> Your old computers, laptops, and peripherals can help bridge the digital divide.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      <strong>Volunteer:</strong> Join our skilled team to help refurbish and distribute computers to those in need.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      <strong>Support Us:</strong> Purchasing from our eBay store helps fund our operations and sustainability efforts.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Contact Us</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For more information, visit our <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">About Us</a> page,
      browse our <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Computers for Sale</a> section, or explore the menu above.
    </p>

  </section>

